## PREAMBLE: THE NUCLEUS AS GEOMETRIC ANALOGY

The Hero 93 framework explores the nucleus as a **geometric condensation** within the 93‑node solid. This document offers a vocabulary for seeing patterns, not a replacement for nuclear physics.

---

## PART I: HADRONIC INTERPRETATIONS (TIER 3)

### I.1 The Proton as the 93‑Node Solid

The proton is the **93‑point solid itself**, manifested in the hadronic scale. Its mass ≈ 938 MeV/$c^2$ corresponds to the **volume** ($V_{93}=42$) of the solid. The three quarks correspond to the **three rings** (A, B, C) of the 93‑node matrix, each containing 31 nodes.

### I.2 The Neutron as Parity‑Flipped Configuration

The neutron differs from the proton by a **parity flip** of one ring, resulting in a neutral charge ($+\frac{2}{3} - \frac{1}{3} - \frac{1}{3} = 0$). The mass difference $\Delta m \approx 1.3$ MeV/$c^2$ is the energy of the **12.37% gap** scaled to the nuclear scale.

